  "prompt": "How did Kakashi get the Sharingan?",
  "response": "Kakashi got his Sharingan from his teammate, Obito Uchiha, during the Third Shinobi World War. Here's the breakdown:\n\n*   **Team Minato:** Kakashi, Obito, and Rin were teammates under the leadership of Minato Namikaze (later the Fourth Hokage).\n*   **Mission Gone Wrong:** During a mission in Kusagakure (Grass Country), the team was ambushed by enemy ninja.\n*   **Saving Kakashi:** Obito awakened his Sharingan (though initially only with one tomoe) while trying to protect Kakashi. He then pushed Kakashi out of the way of a falling boulder.\n*   **Obito's Sacrifice:** The boulder crushed Obito's right side, leaving him mortally wounded.\n*   **Obito's Gift:** As a dying wish, Obito asked Rin, who was a medical-nin, to transplant his left Sharingan (which was undamaged) into Kakashi's damaged left eye socket, as a gift to celebrate Kakashi's promotion to Jonin.\n*   **Kakashi's Sharingan:** The transplant was successful, and Kakashi received Obito's Sharingan.\n\nBecause Kakashi is not an Uchiha by blood, he can't deactivate the Sharingan. This means he constantly drains chakra from its use, which is why he often has to conserve energy. This also earned him the nickname \"Copy Ninja Kakashi,\" as he uses the Sharingan to copy enemy jutsu.\n",
